{
  "stem": "17001.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And there were times that we would fatten up the goose, take it to the [NON-ENGLISH], clean it, and everything kosher.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then I would take it to a big city, Ungvar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when I get off the train, I would go walk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And as I'm walking, I heard some Jewish spoken people on this street, so I would approach them and I said, look.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I have here this certificate from the-- the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "This is a kosher goose.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And if you like to buy it, I sell it to you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she bought it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were very happy, very delighted to-- to buy kosher goose.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the meantime, the money what I received for it, I was able to buy material to make a dress, to make a shirt, and things like that, so it was like black market-y sort of.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Do you think that your family ever considered leaving Hungary?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- it never was mentioned.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It never came to our mind, because what happened is that my mother's sisters and brothers were all in United State.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were supposed to come in '37.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had the affidavit.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had all the papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then my brother was born.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when my brother was born, we had to send back the papers to have one extra name put on it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "By the time the paper arrived, it was '38 and all the border were closed, so we were stuck in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We-- we-- we couldn't think of going anywhere by that time, because we couldn't go.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was-- it was a pretty big mark on us, because we were all prepared to come to United State.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, it-- it was a lot of difficult years, lot of difficult time being a Jew in-- in those days in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
